race.comment: ALTHOFF (7) has continued to build beautifully this campaign and can keep the roll going as he chases the hat-trick. Grima sticks with the 3kg claim and should have him blending into the race perfectly. Will take plenty of holding out. SOVEREIGN HILL (17) is airborne chasing his own hat-trick and will give another bold sight in front, though he won't get it all his own way this time. POLYMNIA (12) resumes and, while yet to strike fresh, she gets McDonald from a good draw and should appreciate the anticipated tempo. Two trials have her ready to break a long run of outs. AERODROME (14) is a promising 3YO resuming with a fresh win already on the resum√© and a recent trial that saw him savaging the line. He must be considered. CLOUDLAND (3) boasts a terrific fresh record, including a barnstorming FU win at Rosehill last prep over 1200m. He'll let them roll and look to swoop late.
